{
  "texts": [
    "Below, we shall see that for the minimal tension string, the Wakimoto construction plays a more direct (and possibly complete) role.",
    "Specifically, we will see that the OPEs for this representation will arise in an exact form, not as an approximation in the large Φ limit.",
    "Given that the k = 1 string is most naturally described in twistor variables, one might anticipate that the adapted variables of the Wakimoto construction provide a more natural spacetime interpretation in light of (2.13).",
    "Recovering spacetime: Wakimoto from bosonizationTo make contact with the Wakimoto representation, it is useful to bosonize the free fields as in [15].",
    "This gives an explicit way of realising the k = 1 theory in terms of spacetime physics."
  ]
}